race.comment: BUTWEDID (3) quickly found form belting a Maiden field at Murwillumbah from the front backed off the map. He is still shy of his best and will be fitter again. He will use the inside barrier and looks capable of taking the next step. DOITLIKEMAXWELL (4) did a good job when beaten a whisker here on debut and then didn't finish it off stepping up to this trip in a CL2 at Dalby without much support. This grade suits him much better, and he's proven himself third-up. He rates to be right in it. THUNDEROUS (6) has been busting to win since his easy 58 win at Lismore. The speedy galloper may be the one to control the races, and he also has winning claims. HUSSON'S REVENGE (13) has the ability but is hard to catch. Wouldn't be far way putting his best foot forward.
